    <h1>Blazor Icon</h1>
    <p>A material icon component.</p>
    <p>We know, you are thinking, "Who needs a component for rendering a simple icon?"</p>
    <p>
      And you would be right...except an ordinary html <code class="@codeBG">&lt;i&gt;&lt;/i&gt;</code> tag doesn't come with built-in sizes or themes, 
      such as dark and light modes, now does it?
    </p>
    <p>Go ahead. Hit this button <Icon Variant="invert_colors" class="cursor-pointer" @onclick="@((e) => MainLayout.ToggleTheme())" /> and watch how <i>all</i> the icons change colors.</p>
    <p>See what we mean? And that's not all. This component can keep state should the need arise.</p>

